      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UTAH ICON (3) turned in a plain run last time when seventh at The Meadows over 525m behind Fromelles Poppy (30.95) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Has ability and looks hard to stop. PAW WELKES (5) showed blistering pace early and gave a sight when in the minors, beaten 2.5 lengths over 450m this track in 25.27. Leading chance. PAT'S BOY (1) resumed from a break finishing sixth (25.58) at this track in a Grade 4/5. Has a good record here including five wins. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in two starts. Should be in this for a long way. BAROOGA KING (2) can measure up with the right run.",
